-/

/-- Standard Borel structure on `(‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ)`. Mathlib v4.28 provides
this via `Pi.standardBorelSpace` for countable index types over
standard Borel factors; pinned here as an instance for downstream
SubGaussianMG construction. -/
noncomputable instance : @StandardBorelSpace (‚Ąē ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ) canonicalMeasurableSpace := by
  sorry

/-! ## Strengthened sharpness witness

The non-degenerate-witness form of the matching-lower-bound
adversary: an explicit `SubGaussianMG` whose process is
`gaussianWalk` (not any inhabitant). Constructed by feeding the
five hypotheses above into `Pythia.one_d_marginal_reduction_tight`.

If any of the five hypothesis-helpers above is closed, this
theorem becomes correspondingly more axiom-clean. The current
sorry resolves to the conjunction of the five named sorries,
making per-helper progress visible.
-/

/-- The iid-standard-Gaussian random walk realises the Pythia
`SubGaussianMG` structure with parameter `ŌÉ`, and the structure's
`process` field is `gaussianWalk` (forbidding the constant /
zero-process degenerate inhabitants the `Nonempty` form admits). -/
theorem gaussianWalk_isSubGaussianMG (ŌÉ : ‚ĄĚ) (hŌÉ : 0 < ŌÉ) :
    ‚ąÉ M : SubGaussianMG ŌÉ canonicalFiltration
            (gaussianProductMeasure ŌÉ),
      M.process = gaussianWalk :=
  Pythia.one_d_marginal_reduction_tight hŌÉ gaussianWalk
    gaussianWalk_adapted
    (gaussianWalk_integrable ŌÉ)
    (gaussianWalk_increments_subG ŌÉ hŌÉ)
    (gaussianWalk_integrable_exp ŌÉ)
    (gaussianWalk_increments_zero_mean ŌÉ)

/-- Legacy weak Nonempty form. Kept for backward-compat with
existing downstream callers; consumers should switch to
`gaussianWalk_isSubGaussianMG`. -/
theorem gaussianWalk_subGaussianMG (ŌÉ : ‚ĄĚ) (hŌÉ : 0 < ŌÉ) :
    Nonempty (SubGaussianMG ŌÉ canonicalFiltration
      (gaussianProductMeasure ŌÉ)) :=
  ‚ü®(gaussianWalk_isSubGaussianMG ŌÉ hŌÉ).choose‚ü©

end Pythia
